The paper discusses the design and security analysis of a linear code based encryption scheme, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The scheme also involves the use of coding theory concepts such as random linear codes, which could be classified under information theory (cs.IT) and error-correcting codes (cs.CC). The paper also mentions several cryptanalysis techniques, which could be classified under cybersecurity (cs.CY) and security engineering (cs.SE).
